column5: Probably Lew. Here's a typical autumn CH pose with the evidence shown clearly:   That CH sure knows how to pose with the muskies....here's another from River X

gald to have you on my boat Jamie , always a good time LOL  Acouple more pics  Teeth    And the release    Too bad about that non movable that took those nice chunks out of my plow ----we'll get her next year Jamie.  Anytime Bud  Matt

Great stuff Matt....but of course with Jamie after 10 months we still haven't got it thru his head....OFC logo !!!! We needed a 'ski for team 5 !..oh and probably those ugly Carp he was chasin this year as well.
Your right Chris, Jamies definetely the Dawg King when it comes to toothies, he even brought his talents with him when we fished the K-Lakes this summer
LOL we caught two in the spot last week Chris!   that fish was on the legend perch bait...  thanks Lew!

Why is everything top secret????? Only a few guys actually say where or how they caught the fish. It'd be nice if people expanded on their story (at least when asked). I'm not looking for GPS coordinates. Maybe what lake or area and especially conditions,water clarity and what you used to catch them (equipment ,live bait or crankbait,spinner etc.). If it was lure,what type,colour,pattern etc. ? How's a guy supposed to learn? I'm not looking to steal "your fish", just learn how to catch my own.
QUOTE "that fish was on the legend perch bait..."
Nice looking 'ski CH! Definately a great way to end the year   , congrats!
Pm sent   Matt
Congrats on that! I love those "toothy" pics.  Pete

hey man... I have no problems sharing technics , if there is anything you want to know , PM me... I am always willing to answer any questions. it was not a record fish thought I would share the pic and thank Matt...i did mention what I caught it on in the thread
Nice looking fish, well done.

broke my fall streak and helped me put a 40" fish in the boat...  sorry about the SLOB you lost.. she will be fatter next year  had a blast out on the water, thanks again you are a great guy to spend a day on the boat with.
Pics!
Nice one man!
beauty ch!
wtg, that's a nice 'ski to break your streak...  Mike
nice pic man. congrats  cheers and great fishing!
Any time on the water is good this time of year. Nice fish.
Nice picks .I am yet to catch my first Muskie.All I ever catch is Pike.Thats why my friends called Me Mike the Pike.
Next year is when I'd love to target those big boys!!!  Gotta upgrade my gear thought.  Something tells me that my 30 dollar CTC combo wont do it...LOL.  Great lookin fish!
Great stuff Jamie!!! Gonna ask you the same old question. OFC logo in any shots....
That one will help you sleep well untill the spring, nice one.  Did you get a good look at the one that got away ? there usually alot bigger, lol....
dawg ??
Nice fish CH   .  Congrats
Congrats Jamie! Nice looking fish bud.  Whopper
Nice fish CH, WTG man !!
Always nice when you manage to catch one this late in the season. Way to go Jamie.
great looking ski!!!!  Cheers!
Congrats on ending the streak!
thanks for the report...and thats a nice musky wtg
Beaut! Congrats on your late season ski.  Cheers, 1leg
nice work Crazy!  cheers uf
Congrats on your breaking your 'ski streak!  I'll have to wait until next year for me to attempt for my first 'ski.  WTG!
That sure is a beauty gator,congrats. What did you catch it on and where? We need the rest of the story (or at least I do). PLEASE LOL.
Way to go CH. Beautiful fish there it has really nice colours.
